.TH _PRINTF 3 « 2025-11-28 » Holberton project

.SH NAME _printf
Implementation of the printf function (simplified version) in C language

.SH SYNOPSIS 
.nf
#include "main.h"
.fi

.nf
int _printf(const char *format, ...);
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION 
It displays text on standard output and supports format specifiers :
.TP
%c
Display a character

.TP
%s
Display a string

.TP
%%
Display the % symbol

.TP
%i
Display an integer

.TP
%d
Display an integer

.SH RETURN VALUE 
The number of characters printed

.SH EXAMPLES 
.SS Display text
.nf
printf("Hello world!");
.fi
It's displayed : Hello world!

.SS Display a character
.nf
printf("The character is : %c", 'A');
.fi
It's displayed : The character is : A

.SS Display a string
.nf
printf("The string is : %s", "Holberton School");
.fi
It's displayed : The string is : Holberton School

.SS Display the % symbol
.nf
printf("The score is 100%%");
.fi
It's displayed : The score is 100%

.SS Display an integer
.nf
printf("I have %i projects", 2);
.fi
It's displayed : I have 2 projects

.SS Display an integer
.nf
printf("the deficit is at %d dollars", -100000);
.fi
It's displayed : the deficit is at -100000 dollars

.SH AUTHOR
Veronique BEAUVAIS and Mateo MARQUES
